5 A BILL
6 TO BE ENTITLED
7 AN ACT
8
9 Relating to health insurance; to set requirements on
10 reimbursement rates by health care insurers for ground
11 ambulance services, with exceptions; to provide that the
12 established reimbursement rate is payment in full for ground
13 ambulance services; to impose reporting requirements by
14 emergency medical service providers that provide ground
15 ambulance services and health care insurers to the Alabama
16 Department of Public Health; to provide for a report on the
17 effects of this act, with recommendations for improving access
18 to emergency medical transport; and to provide for repeal of
19 this act.
20 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
21 Section 1. For the purposes of this act, the following
22 words have the following meanings:
23 (1) CLEAN CLAIM. A clean electronic claim or a clean
24 written claim.
25 (2) CLEAN ELECTRONIC CLAIM. As defined in Section
26 27-1-17, Code of Alabama 1975.
27 (3) CLEAN WRITTEN CLAIM. As defined in Section 27-1-17,
28 Code of Alabama 1975.
