29 (4) COLLECTION. Any written or oral communication made
30 to an enrollee for the purpose of obtaining payment for the
31 services rendered by an emergency medical service provider,
32 including invoicing and legal debt collection efforts.
33 (5) COST-SHARING AMOUNT. The enrollee's deductible,
34 coinsurance, copayment, or other amount due under a health
35 care benefit plan for covered services.
36 (6) COVERED SERVICES or COVERED SERVICE. Transport or
37 medical services provided by the ground ambulance of an
38 emergency medical service provider which are covered by an
39 enrollee's health care benefit plan, which may include
40 emergency ground transport and treat in place.
41 (7) EMERGENCY GROUND TRANSPORT. a. When an enrollee is
42 transported by an emergency medical service provider to a
43 hospital or definitive care facility as defined in Section
44 22-18-1, Code of Alabama 1975, and which may include basic
45 life support or advanced life support, in response to a
46 medical condition described in paragraph b.
47 b. An event as defined by the Centers for Medicare and
48 Medicaid Services (CMS) that manifests itself by acute
49 symptoms of sufficient severity, including severe pain, such
50 that a prudent layperson, who possesses an average knowledge
51 of health and medicine, could reasonably expect the absence of
52 immediate medical attention to result in:
53 1. Placing the patient's health in serious jeopardy;
54 2. Serious impairment to bodily functions; or
55 3. Serious dysfunction of any bodily organ or part.
56 (8) EMERGENCY MEDICAL SERVICE PROVIDER or PROVIDER. Any
