Substitute for HB400
57 public or private organization that is licensed to provide
58 emergency medical services as defined in Section 22-18-1, Code
59 of Alabama 1975.
60 (9) ENROLLEE. An individual who is covered by a health
61 care benefit plan.
62 (10) HEALTH CARE BENEFIT PLAN. a. The term includes
63 any individual or group plan, policy, or contract issued,
64 delivered, or renewed in this state by a health care insurer
65 to provide, deliver, arrange for, pay for, or reimburse health
66 care services, including those provided by an emergency
67 medical service provider, except for payments for health care
68 made under automobile or homeowners' insurance plan,
69 accident-only plan, specified disease plan, long-term care
70 plan, supplemental hospital or fixed indemnity plan, dental or
71 vision plan, or Medicaid.
72 b. The term does not include any plan that pays or
73 reimburses for health care services, including those provided
74 by an emergency medical service provider, pursuant to Chapter
75 25A of Title 16, Code of Alabama 1975, or Chapter 29 of Title
76 36, Code of Alabama 1975.
77 (11) HEALTH CARE INSURER. Any entity that issues or
78 administers a health care benefit plan, including a health
79 care insurer, a health care services plan incorporated under
80 Chapter 20 of Title 10A, Code of Alabama 1975, a health
81 maintenance organization established under Chapter 21A of
82 Title 27, Code of Alabama 1975, or a nonprofit agricultural
83 organization that offers health benefits to its membership
84 pursuant to Chapter 33 of Title 2, Code of Alabama 1975.
