169 standard electronic health insurance claim format designated
170 by Section 27-1-16, Code of Alabama 1975.
171 b. Information or data elements in excess of those
172 required on the standard health insurance claim form
173 designated by Section 27-1-16, Code of Alabama 1975.
174 (4) Any dispute between a health care insurer and an
175 emergency medical service provider over the amount to be paid,
176 or over full or partial denial of a claim, may be settled by:
177 a. Affording the provider access to the insurer's
178 internal forum for resolving provider disputes concerning
179 coverage and reimbursement amounts; and
180 b. If the dispute is not resolved in the insurer's
181 internal forum, submission of the dispute to an independent
182 dispute resolution contractor selected by mutual agreement of
183 the insurer and the provider.
184 Section 4. (a) Beginning in the year 2027, and in each
185 year thereafter, an emergency medical service provider shall
186 submit to the Alabama Department of Public Health a report
187 that includes, but is not limited to, the following
188 information for the preceding calendar year:
189 (1) The number and type of emergency medical service
190 vehicles that are in service.
191 (2) The number of employees, both full-time and
192 part-time, classified by position or emergency medical service
193 provider license classification.
194 (3) The total number of ground ambulance transports
195 rendered.
196 (4) The average response time for collecting and
