201 distributes ownership shares to the public, the number and
202 amount of dividends issued.
203 (7) For the calendar year 2027, the amount of receipts
204 collected by the emergency medical service provider that are
205 remitted to a parent entity, both before and after
206 implementation of any change in payment or reimbursement by a
207 health care insurer.
208 (8) For the calendar year 2027, the amount paid or
209 reimbursed to an emergency medical service provider by health
210 care insurers, presented on a monthly or quarterly basis.
211 (b)(1) Beginning in the year 2027, a health care
212 insurer shall submit to the Alabama Department of Public
213 Health a report on claims for reimbursement submitted by
214 emergency medical service providers which presents, for each
215 of the three calendar years preceding January 1, 2027:
216 a. The number of denied claims;
217 b. The aggregate dollar value of denied claims;
218 c. The percentage of denied claims to approved claims;
219 d. The applicable out-of-pocket charge under each
220 health care benefit plan issued by the health care insurer on
221 an approved claim for covered services; and
222 e. The total amount paid on claims for covered
223 services, including in comparison to the total amount paid out
224 on all claims for health care services.
